Initial analysis of trends in reported zoonoses

Joshua Blake

2024-05-20

library(purrr)
library(readr)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(tidyr)
raw_data_loc = here::here("data", "raw/")

This file contains a look at the number of reported emerging infectious diseases across several papers. Some simple plots and models, not accounting for reporting effort.

Plot counts per year since 1940 with different minimum number of deaths. Note HIV and SARS-CoV-2 pandemics are excluded from this dataset.

min_deaths = c(-10000, 0.1, 1, 10)
raw_marani |>
    filter(`Start Year` >= 1940) |>
    group_by(`Start Year`) |>
    reframe(
        min_deaths = min_deaths,
        n = purrr::map_int(min_deaths, ~sum(`# deaths (thousands)` >= .x))
    ) |>
    complete(
        `Start Year` = 1940:2020,
        min_deaths,
        fill = list(n = 0)
    ) |>
    ggplot(aes(`Start Year`, n)) +
    facet_wrap(~min_deaths) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    labs(
        x = "Year",
        y = "Number of events",
        color = "Minimum deaths"
    )

Not that much different, we’ll go with 1000 deaths as the minimum. Although, the decline when including all events suggests that maybe reporting isn’t an issue.

marani_counts = raw_marani |>
    filter(`Start Year` >= 1940) |>
    filter(`# deaths (thousands)` >= 1) |>
    count(year = `Start Year`) |>
    mutate(dataset = "marani")

Tan data

Take the data from Tan et al. (2014) and count the number of events per year. Years were annotated by Phil Palmer, two are missing which will be excluded.

tan_counts = read_csv(paste0(raw_data_loc, "zoonotic_events_with_year.csv")) |>
    filter(!is.na(Year)) |>
    count(year = Year) |>
    mutate(dataset = "tan")

Basic plots

all_counts = bind_rows(marani_counts, tan_counts, jones_counts, munguia_counts) |>
    group_by(dataset) |>
    complete(year = full_seq(year, 1), fill = list(n = 0)) |>
    ungroup()

all_counts |>
    ggplot(aes(year, n, color = dataset)) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    labs(
        x = "Year",
        y = "Number of events",
        color = "Dataset"
    )

Simple GLM

glm_fits = all_counts |>
    group_nest(dataset) |>
    mutate(
        model = map(data, ~glm(n ~ year, data = .x, family = quasipoisson)),
        # add R2 and confidence interval for the slope
        summary = map(model, broom::glance),
        # r2 = map_dbl(summary, "r.squared", 1),
        tidy = map(model, broom::tidy, conf.int = TRUE),
        slope = map_dbl(tidy, ~filter(., term == "year")$estimate),
        slope_ci_low = map_dbl(tidy, ~filter(., term == "year")$conf.low),
        slope_ci_high = map_dbl(tidy, ~filter(., term == "year")$conf.high),
        slope_p_value = map_dbl(tidy, ~filter(., term == "year")$p.value),
        augmented = map(model, broom::augment, se_fit = TRUE),
    ) |>
    unnest(summary)

glm_fits |>
    select(dataset, deviance, contains("slope"))
## # A tibble: 4 × 6
##   dataset deviance   slope slope_ci_low slope_ci_high slope_p_value
##   <chr>      <dbl>   <dbl>        <dbl>         <dbl>         <dbl>
## 1 jones      109.   0.0141      0.00382        0.0246      9.83e- 3
## 2 marani      74.1 -0.0282     -0.0477        -0.0103      3.95e- 3
## 3 munguia    432.  -0.0109     -0.0417         0.0198      4.94e- 1
## 4 tan        192.   0.0477      0.0373         0.0591      2.81e-13
glm_fits |>
    unnest(augmented) |>
    ggplot(aes(year, exp(.fitted), color = dataset)) +
    geom_line() +
    geom_point(aes(y = n)) +
    # facet_wrap(~dataset, scales = "free_y") +
    # uncertainty ribbon for the line
    geom_ribbon(
        aes(ymin = exp(.fitted - 1.96 * .se.fit), ymax = exp(.fitted + 1.96 * .se.fit),
            colour = NULL, group = dataset),
        alpha = 0.2
    ) +
    labs(
        x = "Year",
        y = "Number of events",
        color = "Dataset"
    )

glm_fits |>

    ggplot(aes(year, exp(.fitted), color = dataset)) +

            colour = NULL, group = dataset),
        alpha = 0.2
    ) +
    labs(
        x = "Year",
        y = "Number of events",
        color = "Dataset"
    )

base_year = 1950

Plot each trend, setting the value at 1950 to 1.

# cartesian product of datasets and years
expand_grid(
    dataset = unique(all_counts$dataset),
    year = base_year:2020,
) |>
    left_join(glm_fits, by = "dataset") |>
    mutate(
        n = exp((year - base_year) * slope),
        n_low = exp((year - base_year) * slope_ci_low),
        n_high = exp((year - base_year) * slope_ci_high),
    ) |>
    ggplot(aes(year, n, color = dataset)) +
    geom_line() +
    geom_ribbon(
        aes(ymin = n_low, ymax = n_high, colour = NULL, group = dataset),
        alpha = 0.2
    ) +
    labs(
        x = "Year",
        y = "Number of events",
        color = "Dataset"
    )
